FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_CUSTOM_EVENT_NAME

Key of the details dictionary passed to -[FWRendererController processEvent::]. Its value is the custom event name to be processed.

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_CUSTOM_ID

Key of FW_NOTIFICATION_SLOT_STARTED & FW_NOTIFICATION_SLOT_ENDED notification's userInfo dictionary. Its value is slot's custom id.

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_ERROR

Key of FW_NOTIFICATION_REQUEST_COMPLETE notification's userInfo dictionary.

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_ERROR_CODE

Key of the info dictionary in -[FWRendererController handleStateTransition:FW_RENDERER_STATE_FAILED info:details]. Its value is FW_ERROR_*

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_ERROR_INFO

Key of the info dictionary in -[FWRendererController handleStateTransition:FW_RENDERER_STATE_FAILED info:details]. Its value is the error's detailed description message.

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_ERROR_MODULE

Key of the info dictionary in -[FWRendererController handleStateTransition:FW_RENDERER_STATE_FAILED info:details]. Its value is FW_MODULE_TYPE_*

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_MODULE_TYPE

Key of the dictionary returned by -[FWRenderer moduleInfo]. Its value is FW_MODULE_TYPE_*

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_REQUIRED_API_VERSION

Key of the dictionary returned by =[FWRenderer moduleInfo]. optional, if present, its value should be the lowest SDK API version the renderer can compatible e.g. 0x02060000 for v2.6

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_SHOW_BROWSER

Key of the details dictionary passed to -[FWRendererController processEvent::]. Its value is "YES" or @"NO".

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_INFO_KEY_VIDEO_DISPLAY_BASE

Key of FW_NOTIFICATION_VIDEO_DISPLAY_BASE_CHANGED & FW_NOTIFICATION_VIDEO_DISPLAY_BASE_FRAME_CHANGED notification's userInfo dictionary. Its value is the videoDisplayBase object set by API [FWContext setVideoDisplayBase:].

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_PARAMETER_DESIRED_ORIENTATION

The key of available desired orientation of rendition selection algorithm. It only takes effect in full screen mode.
The value of this property is a NSString.

  • If it is not set, the application status bar orientation is used.
  • It can be set to one of @"portrait" and @"landscape".
    • If it is set to @"portrait", the smaller of UIScreen width and height will be selected as width and the bigger of UIScreen width and height will be selected as height.
    • The @"landscape" is opposite to @"portrait".

FW_EXTERN NSString* const FW_PARAMETER_IN_APP_VIEW_TOOLBAR_SURFACE_RENDER

The key of InAppView ToolBar surface render parameter.
The value of the parameter is a string of Html5 which will be injected into the surface web page of the ToolBar .
The following template is suggested to use:

<div>
<div style=""><img ID="FW_IN_APP_VIEW_CONTROL_BAR_BACK_BUTTON" src="data:image/png;base64,PNG_BASE64_STRING" width="" height=""/></div>
<div style=""><img ID="FW_IN_APP_VIEW_CONTROL_BAR_FORWARD_BUTTON" src="data:image/png;base64,PNG_BASE64_STRING" width="" height=""/></div>
<div style=""><img ID="FW_IN_APP_VIEW_CONTROL_BAR_CLOSE_BUTTON" src="data:image/png;base64,PNG_BASE64_STRING" width="" height=""/></div>
</div>

The FW_IN_APP_VIEW_CONTROL_BAR_BACK_BUTTON, FW_IN_APP_VIEW_CONTROL_BAR_FORWARD_BUTTON and FW_IN_APP_VIEW_CONTROL_BAR_CLOSE_BUTTON IDs have to be kept as such for handling event.
The all three PNG_BASE64_STRINGs are replaced one by one with each png's base64 string.
The size of img tag and alignment of div tag have to be set properly, e.g. div style can make the close button right aligned.
All Safari mobile compatible html5 tag used in body tag are supported, e.g. utilizing table tag to manage layout instead of div tag.
